  - "② From the data $N_0=10000$, $N(2)=15625$ it follows that $k^2=\\tfrac{15625}{10000}=1.5625$. Hence $k=\\sqrt{1.5625}=1.25$."
  - "③ Hourly increase: $k-1=0.25$, i.e. $25\\%$."
tests:
  log_exp: 1.0
  fn_exp: 0.5
