hintEn: "Step by step:\\n\\n① FACTOR: numerator = $(x-5)$, denominator = $(x-2)$. Already factored.\\n\\n② ZEROS: numerator = 0 → $x = 5$. Denominator = 0 → $x = 2$ (EXCLUDED — division by 0!).\\n\\n③ DO WE INCLUDE THE ENDPOINTS?\\n• $x = 5$: fraction = $0/3 = 0$, and $0 \\leq 0$ ✓ → INCLUDE (square bracket])\\n• $x = 2$: denominator = 0 → ALWAYS EXCLUDE (round bracket)\\n\\n④ SIGN TABLE — critical points: $2$ and $5$:\\n• $x < 2$ (e.g. $x=0$): $\\frac{-5}{-2} = +2.5$ → positive ✗\\n• $2 < x < 5$ (e.g. $x=3$): $\\frac{-2}{1} = -2$ → negative ✓\\n• $x > 5$ (e.g. $x=6$): $\\frac{1}{4}$ → positive ✗\\n\\n⑤ ANSWER: negative or zero on $(2, 5]$. Round bracket at $2$ (denominator=0), square bracket at $5$ (numerator=0, fraction=0 ✓)."
