hintEn: "The axial cross-section of a cylinder is a rectangle with sides $2r = 2$ and $h = 2\\sqrt{3}$. The diagonal forms a right triangle with the base side, in which $\\tan \\alpha = h / 2r = 2\\sqrt{3} / 2 = \\sqrt{3}$. Hence $\\alpha = 60°$."
